        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         numm do NOT run 2k or NT or even XP unless you are doing dual boot!</P><P>the NT technology has a lot of problems with games, you will have 100% cpu usage whenever you play games and the entire system will crawl!</P><P>anyways...</P><P>make sure you have the newest via 4in1 drivers (your geforce is agp i think...ask lucann hehe).  if you still have problems after that try downloading the newest drivers from your specific geforce manufacturer (if you download straight from nvidia you can still have problems since it isn't made specifically for your card).</P><P>also, you might want to download a program from Sisoftware called "sandra".  i'll see if i can find a link later.  it has a nice diagnostic program it can run and also in the help file it provides it tells you how to fix any of the problems it lists.<BR>---</P><P>ok sisoftwares main page for <a href="http://www.sisoftware.demon.co.uk/sandra/index.htm" target="_blank">sandra for 9x</a></P><P>here is the main <a href="http://www.sisoftware.demon.co.uk/san_dem/html/dload.htm" target="_blank">download</a> site</P><P>and <a href="http://www.sisoftware.demon.co.uk/san_dem/html/dload_x86.htm" target="_blank">this</a> is the one i believe you would need.</P><P>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML<BR>/rude no HTML</P><P><BR><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu<BR>Inverse Logic</a></P><P>Edited by - Abillister_Abu on 06/11/2002  20:23:16</P><P>Edited by - Abillister_Abu on 06/11/2002  20:23:58<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
