        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I agree NT sucked for games.  I used Win 2K for about a year and a half and I had a few issues with games (notably EQ when they did a DX upgrade before Velious).  With Win XP I have had no issues with any games and neither have any of my friends.  Games manufacturers have to design games to work on XP now as new branded PCs all come with this.</P><P>XP is completely stable. 2K is completely stable (had a home built server run for 18 months without being rebooted).  The only reason you might suffer instability is if you install some wierd funky stuff on it like beta device drivers.</P><P>As Numm seems to be mainly interested in games my opinion would be go with Win XP if her PC is powerful enough.  If not go with W98.</P><P>Just so you know the machines I'm using (both hand built):</P><P>Asus A7V266E<BR>AthlonXP 1900+ (1.6GHz)<BR>768MB DDRRAM<BR>GF3 Ti500</P><P>ABIT KT7A<BR>Duron 750 o/c 900<BR>768MB SDRAM<BR>GF2 MX</P><P>Oh, my work PC with WinXP blue-screened a couple of times till I realised the people who had put it together had put the fan so it blew air in rather than out and was overheating it hehe.</P><P><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=16832" TARGET="_NEW">Draknn Fels, Warlock</A><BR>Divide et Impera, Bristlebane<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
